Patching : To update your linux system / To keep your system up to dated
	1. Stop app/web services (systemctl stop httpd)
	2. Stop DB services (Systemctl stop mysqld) 
	3. Patching : (yum update -y) 
	4. Sanity check (uptime/who -b/uname -r/a)
	5. Start DB (systemctl start mysqld)
	6. Start app (systemctl start httpd/gitlabd)

System packages 
Security Packages 

Kernel also get up to dated if there is release
System gets rebooted if required or kernel installed

